Res perere et captos ostendere civibus hostes, &a “ To perform exploits, and to show the citizens their foes led captive, reaches the throne of J ove, and aspires to celestial honours : '' i. e. is mounting up to the throne of Jupiter, and treading the paths of immortality. The expression captos ostendere civibus hostes alludes to the solemnity of a Roman triumph.
